  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIn the course of the[ Medalla Incident](https://medium.com/prysmatic-labs/eth2-medalla-testnet-incident-f7fbc3cc934a), a large number of validators got slashed. A large amount of those validators were running with docker and forgot to specify the volume for the validator db. This lead to a new db being created on each restart. \r\n\r\nHowever a subset were also running local slashing protection on a persistent db. This did not succeed for a few validators leading them to be slashed.\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\nAlpha.21\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n \r\nAttached are the DBs. \r\n1:\r\nPubkey: `0xae2a8200081ebc3d5b75cfaa25ea648d795585b1b0e32e128c09fc6f16f950d098c9df1e5a092b55f13c382884ac38fe`\r\n\r\nhttps://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/746233394903515208/746238513548099586/validator.db\r\n\r\n2:\r\nhttps://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/476588476393848832/745948302695989258/validator.db\r\n\r\n3:\r\nhttps://beaconcha.in/validator/9556\r\nhttps://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/667761857209040916/746213204073512960/validator.db\r\n\r\n",
